As a foreign student in India from 1970-1988, I saw extreme poverty in India during the reign of the corrupt, minority-appeasement Congress party. As a foreigner, when I visited India 2 years ago, I got the chance to use my 1st public toilet in India, which did not exist during the more than 60 years old of corrupt Congress reign. Shame on the dynasty party for destroying India for so many years - you taught us in our Indian school that it is okay to be poor because of population explosion. China proved the corrupt Congress party otherwise - this is when Indians woke up. it’s the fault of our parents who voted blindly for the once respected Congress party that belonged to our great Mahatma Gandhi. The present youth of India and their parents have finally woken up from their slumber about the Sonia-Vadra Congress. Long live India, and the capable BJP Party.

snippet.textDisplay:
I'm from Canada and I think China is a bully. China keeps saying it wants to occupy Taiwan. It is stripping people in Hong Kong of rights that were guaranteed in the one country two systems arrangement. It has built artificial islands to lay claims to the South China Sea. It uses espionage to steal other countries technology. It is rapidly building its armed forces and is preparing for war. China wants to reshape the world with its institutions that do not favour liberty, democracy, or human rights. It is also removing the Uyghur people from their homes and forcing them into concentration camps.

China today is a parallel to Germany and Japan in the 1930's and 1940's. Back then people did want to stand up to those two powerful countries either until late in the game when they finally started their conquest. Indeed many Europeans and Americans supported the NAZIS due to business connections and money they could make. Those two nations also said they were "peaceful" whilst building weapons of war.

People need to wake up and see China for what it really is. The first step would be acknowledging its a threat to all the peaceful nations everywhere especially those in the Asia-Pacific region. The next step should be trade embargoes against the country instead of giving them money so they can build more weapons. Also the nations that favour China should loose access to markets and those that don't should receive more. Also the free nations should start preparing themselves for war because China is not going to abandon its goals or its autocratic communist government.

snippet.textDisplay:
This is a letter from Mr. Ramachandran Nair. He was part of the very first batch from Thrissur (Trichur) Veterinary College and started my career as a veterinary surgeon in 1959 and retired as Director of Animal Husbandry in 1992. This is concerning a totally different topic - that of Kerala's LDF government looting Hindu holy places. Using the excuse of Budget issues during Coronavirus-based lockdown, the CPM-led Left Government in Kerala which manages different temple bodies (Devaswam Boards) are currently taking stock of inventory of all temple assets. The plan is to evaluate what can be sold to get funds for the board. This is being done at a time when people cannot even go out of their homes, let alone protest against these anti-Hindu actions.

Please remember that very rich temples of Sabarimala and Guruvayoor are under the Devaswam Boards. Sri Padmanabhaswamy temple, considered to be one of the richest in the world and now being managed by the Supreme Court had its police protection/security withdrawn. At a time when people are not being allowed to go out, the hurry in unlocking temples and taking stock is only with the malafide intention of indulging in officially sanctioned theft. The CM's answer is that these would be auctioned off only with the permission of Kerala High Court, but he is not talking of the antiques and their values. The concern is that all the expensive items would be stolen first during the time people are not being allowed to visit the temples. Only the low-value items would be listed for auction.

We have already seen the Kerala government forcefully taking away Rs 5 crore to the Corona Fund from the fixed deposits of Guruvayoor Temple. I am sharing this because there is no other hope than the Central Government's intervention for Hindu believers to protect their temples and the assets within them. The plan is to evaluate what can be sold to get funds for the board. This is being done at a time when people cannot even go out of their homes, let alone protest against these anti-Hindu actions.

Sri Padmanabhaswamy temple, considered to be one of the richest in the world and now being managed by the Supreme Court had its police protection/security withdrawn. snippet.textDisplay: How did India become such a polyglot country? Many countries have problems with just two languages--United States (English and Spanish), Canada (English and French), Spain (Spanish and Catalan). Were the gods playing a cruel joke with India by giving her over 26 official languages and more than a thousand unofficial ones? Obviously, this was an evolutionary process that played out over thousands of years. India has managed to survive and thrive--yes, India was a thriving country before the Mughals and English arrived who invaded us only because we were thriving and left us with two more languages. So, do we have a language problem or a problem with language? No, because Indians know instinctively how to bridge communication gaps. I have seen Assamese-Marathi, Tamil-Malayalam , Bengali-Punjabi couples do it. And, if you think it's a problem, can an evolutionary problem be solved by edicts and diktats? Ironically, if we do nothing, most of India will speak Hindi by 2050 by an evolutionary fillip known as Bollywood. Alas, it will be a Hindi amalgamated with Haryanvi, Punjabi, Marathi, Konkani, Tamil, Telugu, Malayalam, Kannada, Bengali, Bhojpuri, Oriya, English. Who knows, in two hundred years we may evolve into a monoglot country. That is, if humanity doesn't self destruct before then.

snippet.textDisplay:
The 3-language policy was recommended by the Kothari Commission in 1968. They recommended that Hindi should be taught in southern states and southern languages should be taught in Hindi states. While all southern states are teaching Hindi (except TN and PY perhaps, I am not sure), not a single Hindi speaking state out of 12 odd has complied. Why??
P.Chidambaram has already clarified that he was only ex-officio chairman of the committee and 28 out of 30 members on the panel were from Hindi/northern states. He did not have a veto to overrule them.
Why is NaMo/BJP/RSS keen on putting this panel recommendation into practice while Kothari Commission recommendation is still catching dust??
Why are there different yardsticks for "nationalism"? If a southerner is expected to learn Hindi for the sake of unity, the northerner should also learn southern languages for the same reason.
If a southerner has to speak Hindi when he goes North and still speak Hindi when a northerner comes South, then our languages will certainly die, given the massive south bound migration in recent times. This is a recipe for harakiri.
All Central Govt schemes are in Hindi now. All parliamentary debates are in Hindi now. All minsters and dignitaries are being asked to speak in Hindi. It is expected that Hindi students should be allowed to take interviews in Hindi in any part of this country. I am a Kannadiga and I love my language. I also want to spoken to only in Kannada no matter where I go in this country and similarly other language speakers. Can the President please give his nod?
Modi/BJP/RSS are actually trying to kill English in this country and give that slot to Hindi. Everyone today knows how important English is. If NaMo kills English, we will end up selling tea at VadNagar railway station like our honourable PM once did.
We southerners will never give up our language and culture for Hindi.
We are Indians but we are not Hindi and Modi cannot convert us into Hindi. We will never succumb to becoming 2nd class citizens in our own country and play 2nd fiddle to someone else.
NaMo/BJP/RSS are giving a spur to communal hatred and ultimately division of this country. Sincere advice to Modi...please quit the chauvinism and zealotry and focus on development because you asked us for votes on that basis. Stop trying to implement hidden agendas.

snippet.textDisplay:
Keepalive the fight for justice for Sushant Singh Rajput
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dlycxtCYOCY
my analysis.
1. Sushant Singh Rajput was murdered.
2. It is no way related to Nepotism.
3. Rhea enjoyed his money and she knows Sushant will be killed. She is not related to the murder.
4. Disha’s death related to Sushant’s murder. Disha was a manager and Sushant was a trusted friend to her.
5. Disha was raped by some people in the penthouse party.
6. Disha has seen many powerful people / Underworld people in the party and Adithya Thackeray also and seen some high-level secrets at the party.
7. Disha after coming home and before her death called Sushant Singh and explained what happened at the party. May be sent some proof and photos.
8. Sushant Singh explained this to his friend Siddhartha Pithani and told him that he will open his mouth one day. Siddhartha pithani told to Sandeep Singh that Sushant got full information.
9. Sandeep Singh is a good friend to Sooraj Pancholi. Sandeep told Sooraj Pancholi.
10. They decided to kill Sushant and prepared a plan. A fake film deal was done with Sushant and pressured Sushant to arrange a party.
11. Siddhartha pithani told Rhea what is going to happen on the party night. Rhea left the place.
12. Everything arranged. CCTV to Off managed with Sushant's house workers etc.
13. Sooraj Pancholi, Sandeep Singh was not called for a party. But they attended. Sushant always will be out of drinks, he was in his room reading something.
14. During the party, Siddartha pithani, Sooraj, and one unknown person came from outside went to Sushant’s room and killed him.
15. All left after the party. Second day morning. Adithya Pancholi came to his flat and cleaned up all proofs.
16. Very important point. The opposite apartment CCTV camera captured Aditya Thackeray leaving Sushant’s building. Which was erased after?
snippet.textOriginal:
Keepalive the fight for justice for Sushant Singh Rajput
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dlycxtCYOCY
my analysis.
1.	Sushant Singh Rajput was murdered.
2.	It is no way related to Nepotism.
3.	Rhea enjoyed his money and she knows Sushant will be killed. She is not related to the murder.
4.	Disha’s death related to Sushant’s murder. Disha was a manager and Sushant was a trusted friend to her.
5.	Disha was raped by some people in the penthouse party.
6.	Disha has seen many powerful people / Underworld people in the party and Adithya Thackeray also and seen some high-level secrets at the party.
7.	Disha after coming home and before her death called Sushant Singh and explained what happened at the party. May be sent some proof and photos.
8.	Sushant Singh explained this to his friend Siddhartha Pithani and told him that he will open his mouth one day.  Siddhartha pithani told to Sandeep Singh that Sushant got full information.
9.	Sandeep Singh is a good friend to Sooraj Pancholi. Sandeep told Sooraj Pancholi.
10.	They decided to kill Sushant and prepared a plan. A fake film deal was done with Sushant and pressured Sushant to arrange a party.
11.	Siddhartha pithani told Rhea what is going to happen on the party night. Rhea left the place.
12.	Everything arranged. CCTV to Off managed with Sushant's house workers etc.
13.	Sooraj Pancholi, Sandeep Singh was not called for a party. But they attended. Sushant always will be out of drinks, he was in his room reading something. 
14.	During the party, Siddartha pithani, Sooraj, and one unknown person came from outside went to Sushant’s room and killed him.
15.	All left after the party. Second day morning. Adithya Pancholi came to his flat and cleaned up all proofs.
16.	Very important point. The opposite apartment CCTV camera captured Aditya Thackeray leaving Sushant’s building. Which was erased after?
